🧩 What is HTML?
HTML (HyperText Markup Language) is the standard language used to create web pages.
It defines the structure and layout of a webpage using a system of tags.

🕸️ Example: When you visit any website, what you see (text, images, buttons, forms, etc.) is structured using HTML.

🧱 Basic Structure of an HTML Page
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <title>My First Web Page</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <h1>Hello, World!</h1>
    <p>This is my first HTML page.</p>
  </body>
</html>

Explanation:
<!DOCTYPE html> → tells the browser this is an HTML5 document.
<html> → root of the document.
<head> → contains meta information (like title, CSS, scripts).
<title> → shows in the browser tab.
<body> → contains the visible content.

🏷️ HTML Tags and Elements
🔹 What is a Tag?
Tags are keywords enclosed in angle brackets (< >).
Example:
<p>Paragraph text</p>

🔹 What is an Element?
An element includes the start tag, content, and end tag.

Example:
<p>This is an element.</p>

📚 Commonly Used HTML Tags
Tag	Meaning	Example
<h1> to <h6>	Headings (h1 = largest)	<h1>Main Title</h1>
<p>	Paragraph	<p>This is a paragraph.</p>
<br>	Line Break	Hello<br>World
<hr>	Horizontal line	<hr>
<a>	Hyperlink	<a href="https://google.com">Go to Google</a>
<img>	Image	<img src="photo.jpg" alt="My Photo">
<ul> / <ol>	Unordered / Ordered list	<ul><li>Apple</li></ul>
<table>	Table	<table><tr><td>Data</td></tr></table>
<div>	Division / Section	<div>Content</div>
<span>	Inline container	<span>Text</span>
<form>	User input form	<form><input type="text"></form>

🎨 HTML Attributes
Attributes give extra information about elements.
Example:
<img src="image.jpg" alt="Sample image" width="200" height="100">

Attribute	Description	Example
src	Specifies image source	<img src="img.png">
href	Link URL	<a href="page.html">Link</a>
alt	Alternate text for image	<img alt="logo">
style	Inline CSS styling	<p style="color:red">Text</p>
id	Unique identifier	<div id="main">
class	CSS group name	<div class="box">

🧮 Lists in HTML
Unordered List (bullets):
<ul>
  <li>Apple</li>
  <li>Banana</li>
</ul>

Ordered List (numbers):
<ol>
  <li>First</li>
  <li>Second</li>
</ol>

📊 Tables in HTML
<table border="1">
  <tr>
    <th>Name</th>
    <th>Age</th>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>Apurva</td>
    <td>21</td>
  </tr>
</table>

✏️ Forms in HTML
Used to collect user input (like login or signup forms).
<form action="submit.php" method="post">
  <label>Name:</label>
  <input type="text" name="username"><br>
  <input type="submit" value="Submit">
</form>

🌈 Multimedia Tags
Tag	Purpose	Example
<img>	Display image	<img src="pic.jpg">
<audio>	Play audio	<audio controls src="song.mp3"></audio>
<video>	Play video	<video controls src="movie.mp4"></video>

⚙️ Semantic HTML Tags (HTML5)
These tags make the structure more meaningful:

Tag	Purpose
<header>	Top section of a page
<nav>	Navigation menu
<section>	Section of content
<article>	Independent article or post
<aside>	Sidebar
<footer>	Bottom section (copyright, links, etc.)

💡 HTML Comments
Used to add notes that browsers ignore:
<!-- This is a comment -->

🧠 Advanced Topics
HTML5 APIs:
Include features like:
Geolocation (navigator.geolocation)
Local Storage (localStorage)
Canvas (for drawing)
Drag and Drop
Audio/Video support

Meta Tags (in <head>):
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="description" content="HTML Tutorial">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
Responsive Design: Works with CSS and <meta viewport> for mobile-friendly layouts.

🚀 Summary
Concept	Description
HTML	Structures web pages
Tags	Define elements (like headings, links, etc.)
Attributes	Provide additional info to elements
Forms & Tables	Collect and display data
Semantic tags	Make code cleaner and SEO-friendly
HTML5	Adds modern features (audio, video, APIs)
